paragraphs.text:
%hive
-- Deacceleration event.
--
-- Continuous deacceleration (continuous negative delta velocity over a sequence of seconds) is treated as a single deacceleration event.
SELECT vehicle_id, trip_id, acceleration_group, MIN(acceleration) AS min_acceleration FROM drive_temp
WHERE vehicle_id = 1000500 AND trip_id = "152af94305154e5681323461de8e4ce6"
GROUP BY vehicle_id, trip_id, acceleration_group
HAVING min_acceleration < 0

paragraphs.text:
%hive
-- Hard brakes 10 event.
--
-- Total number of times when hard brakes were applied.
-- Defined as event that exhibits minimum decceleration of less than or equal to -10 m/s
-- Mutliple items that are less than or equal to -10 m/s in a single dececeleration event are counted only once.
SELECT vehicle_id, trip_id, acceleration_group, MIN(acceleration) AS min_acceleration
FROM drive_temp
WHERE vehicle_id = 1000500 AND trip_id = "152af94305154e5681323461de8e4ce6"
GROUP BY vehicle_id, trip_id, acceleration_group
HAVING MIN(acceleration) <= -10

%hive
-- Hard brakes 3 event.
--
-- Total number of times when hard brakes were applied.
-- Defined as event that exhibits minimum decceleration of greater than -10 m/s
-- and less than or equal to -3 m/s.
SELECT vehicle_id, trip_id, acceleration_group, MIN(acceleration) AS min_acceleration
FROM drive_temp
WHERE vehicle_id = 1000500 AND trip_id = "152af94305154e5681323461de8e4ce6"
GROUP BY vehicle_id, trip_id, acceleration_group
HAVING MIN(acceleration) <= -3 AND MIN(acceleration) > -10
